    • getType

      public static BiomeDictionary.Type getType​(String name, BiomeDictionary.Type... subTypes)
      Retrieves a Type instance by name, if one does not exist already it creates one. This can be used as intermediate measure for modders to add their own Biome types.

      There are no naming conventions besides:

      • Must be all upper case (enforced by name.toUpper())
      • No Special characters. {Unenforced, just don't be a pain, if it becomes a issue I WILL make this RTE with no worry about backwards compatibility}

      Note: For performance sake, the return value of this function SHOULD be cached. Two calls with the same name SHOULD return the same value.

      Parameters:
      name - The name of this Type
      Returns:
      An instance of Type for this name.

    • hasType

      public static boolean hasType​(String name)
      Checks if a type instance exists for a given name. Does not have any side effects if a type does not already exist. This can be used for checking if a user-defined type is valid, for example, in a codec which accepts biome dictionary names.
      Parameters:
      name - The name.
      Returns:
      true if a type exists with this name.
      See Also:
      #getType for type naming conventions.

    • getAll
